    <Title>SecureFileUpload.Core — defense-in-depth file upload for ASP.NET Core 8 / 9 / 10</Title>
    <Description>Defense-in-depth file upload pipeline for ASP.NET Core 8, 9, and 10. An 8-layer validation and encrypted-storage pipeline lifted from a production document-intake workflow: size + batch limits, extension allowlist, MIME / extension cross-check, magic-byte signatures, filename inspection, deep structural content validation (JPEG / PNG / WebP walkers + PDF pattern scan with FlateDecode-compressed stream inspection), pluggable virus scanning (Windows Defender or ClamAV), and AES-256-GCM envelope encryption with a per-file random DEK wrapped under an Argon2id-derived master KEK (RFC 9106 / OWASP 2024+). Includes a hardened reference download controller, image recompression to strip polyglot tails, secret-misconfiguration startup guards, and a SharpFuzz / AFL++ harness for the deep content validator. Multi-targets net8.0 / net9.0 / net10.0 — same source, same crypto posture, on every currently-supported .NET runtime. Honest limitations documented in KNOWN-GAPS.md; every security claim traces to source in SECURITY-ANALYSIS.md.</Description>
